<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-27T09:15:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-27T09:15:00-05:00" n="554" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 EW/4–2745: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-27T10:15:00-04:00">April 27,
                                    1945—10:15 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2. Public announcement will be made at noon today by the President, the
                            Prime Minister, and Stalin that the Anglo-American and Soviet forces in
                            Germany have joined at Torgau.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>